TECH_PARAM_1.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number of the beginning of buoyancy reduction (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_3.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached  (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_4.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the beginning of the ascent to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: ascent end time, just before Argos transmission  - note units can vary and the raw values can be in the tech file only if it's not possible to calculate the final JULD in real time.

TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time of the first transmission for this cycle

TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: grounded flag , diagnostic bit - could also be logical?  Yes/no? 0/1? Or can be number of profiles during which the float grounded

TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure recorded just before the previous descent but data is corrected on board the float. Note: cumulative offset but no further correction required. Autocorrected

TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Batteries voltage drop at Pmax, pump ON (with regard to Unom = 10.0 V) (in dV)

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: internal tube temperature at the surface

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Average vertical speed during the descent to parking depth

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Average vertical speed during the ascent to surface

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: real time clock status - 1= OK, 0=not OK

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the cycle (0: nominal, 1: grounding at surface, 2: grounding at pressure shallower than min pressure, 3: max pressure reached during descent, 4: max pressure reached during drift, 5: low battery (less than 6.6V), 6: number of programmed cycle is reached, 10: no programmed date for surfacing after present date, 11: message at deployment, 12 : Mission start again after wait at surface).

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent CTD packets received
TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.
